enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve adding an element to a list, making them suitable for similar test setup scenarios.
The minus method removes an element from a list, which can be used to create a list that can then be tested with the plus method.
The skip method returns a list with elements removed, which can be used to verify the correctness of the plus method by comparing the resulting lists.
The transform method applies a function to each element of a list, which can be used to verify the contents of the list after applying the plus method.
